# GreenSource — Deploy Guide (Render)

Your app is now a real web app: Google sign-in + Stripe subscriptions + server-enforced
free tier (100 beans, 2 calculator uses). This guide gets it live in ~15 minutes.

We'll use **Render.com** (free tier, supports Node, easy). You can use Railway/Fly too —
same idea.

---

## STEP 1 — Put the code on GitHub
1. Create a free account at github.com if you don't have one.
2. Create a new repository called `greensource` (Private is fine).
3. Upload the entire `greensource-backend` folder contents (package.json, server.js,
   db.js, coffee_data.json, and the `public/` folder).
   - Easiest: on the repo page click **Add file -> Upload files**, drag everything in.

## STEP 2 — Create the Render service
1. Go to **render.com** -> sign up (you can sign in with GitHub).
2. Click **New +** -> **Web Service**.
3. Connect your `greensource` GitHub repo.
4. Settings:
   - **Runtime:** Node
   - **Build Command:** `npm install`
   - **Start Command:** `npm start`
   - **Instance type:** Free
5. Click **Create Web Service** (it will build; first build ~2-3 min).

## STEP 3 — Add environment variables
In Render -> your service -> **Environment** -> add each of these
(copy from `.env.example`):

| Key | Value |
|-----|-------|
| GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID | 496092754009-ho2vavhgip5qdm3r8vratiokpiflbvqa.apps.googleusercontent.com |
| STRIPE_SECRET_KEY | your `sk_test_...` secret key |
| STRIPE_PRICE_MONTHLY | price_1ThyXoLXAj1SzqSaVLFTIygw |
| STRIPE_PRICE_YEARLY | price_1ThyYRLXAj1SzqSaHjuxYVVH |
| SESSION_SECRET | any long random string (e.g. mash your keyboard) |
| APP_URL | your Render URL, e.g. https://greensource.onrender.com |

Click **Save, rebuild**. After it redeploys, open your Render URL — the app loads.

## STEP 4 — Tell Google about your real URL
1. Google Cloud Console -> **APIs & Services -> Credentials** -> your "GreenSource Web" client.
2. Under **Authorized JavaScript origins**, click **+ Add URI** and add your Render URL:
   `https://greensource.onrender.com`  (no trailing slash)
3. Save. (Sign-in won't work until this matches your live domain.)

## STEP 5 — Stripe webhook (so paid users unlock instantly)
1. Stripe Dashboard (Test mode) -> **Developers -> Webhooks -> Add endpoint**.
2. Endpoint URL: `https://greensource.onrender.com/api/stripe/webhook`
3. Events to send: select
   - `checkout.session.completed`
   - `customer.subscription.updated`
   - `customer.subscription.deleted`
4. Click **Add endpoint**, then copy the **Signing secret** (`whsec_...`).
5. Back in Render -> Environment -> add `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET = whsec_...` -> Save.

## STEP 6 — Test the whole flow
1. Open your Render URL. You should see ~100 beans + a "422 locked" banner.
2. Click **Sign in with Google** (top-right) -> sign in.
3. Open the **Calculator** twice -> on the 3rd it should show the paywall.
4. Click **Upgrade** -> pick a plan -> use Stripe's **test card** `4242 4242 4242 4242`,
   any future expiry, any CVC, any ZIP.
5. After payment you return to the app as **PRO** — all 522 beans unlock, calculator unlimited.

---

## Going live (real money) — later
- In Stripe, complete **account activation** (bank + business info), switch to **Live mode**,
  recreate the two prices in Live mode, and swap the `sk_live_...` key + live price IDs +
  a live webhook secret into Render. Then flip Google's consent screen to **Published**.

## Notes
- The free tier (100 beans / 2 calc uses) is enforced **on the server**, so it can't be bypassed.
- Calculator usage counts persist per signed-in user. On Render free tier the SQLite file
  resets on redeploy — that's fine (it's generous), and subscription status always re-syncs
  from Stripe. For permanent storage later, add a Render Disk or Postgres (I can help).
- Old tiiny.host site can be retired once this is live.
